    <section id="overview">
        <h2>Overview of Mars</h2>
        <p>Mars is the fourth planet from the Sun and the second-smallest planet in the Solar System after Mercury. It has a thin atmosphere, cold temperatures, and a surface marked by impact craters, volcanoes, valleys, and polar ice caps.</p>
        <p>Its reddish appearance is due to iron oxide prevalent on its surface.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="surface">
        <h2>Surface Features</h2>
        <p>Mars has a diverse range of surface features:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Impact craters</li>
            <li>Volcanoes, including Olympus Mons</li>
            <li>Valleys like Valles Marineris</li>
            <li>Polar ice caps made of water and carbon dioxide</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="rovers">
        <h2>Mars Rovers</h2>
        <p>Several rovers have explored Mars:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Curiosity:</strong> Launched by NASA in 2011, exploring Gale Crater.</li>
            <li><strong>Perseverance:</strong> Launched in 2020, exploring Jezero Crater to search for signs of ancient life.</li>
            <li><strong>Opportunity and Spirit:</strong> Both NASA rovers launched in 2003.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
